## Message Specifications

### Client → Daemon Messages

#### hello - Connection Initialization

```typescript
// Client sends
{
  type: "hello",
  client: "ink" | "web" | "fieldview",
  version?: string  // Optional version info
}

// Daemon responds
{
  type: "hello",
  daemonVersion: string  // e.g., "1.0.0"
}
```

#### start_turn - Start Conversation Turn

```typescript
{
  type: "start_turn",
  input: string,        // User message
  sessionId?: string,   // Optional session ID (UUID)
  mode?: string         // Optional mode override
}
```

#### cancel_turn - Cancel Active Turn

```typescript
{
  type: "cancel_turn",
  turnId: string  // Turn to cancel
}
```

#### list_tools - List Available Tools

```typescript
{
  type: "list_tools"
}

// Response
{
  type: "tools",
  tools: string[]  // Array of tool names
}
```

### Daemon → Client Messages

#### turn_started - Turn Began

```typescript
{
  type: "turn_started",
  sessionId: string,
  turnId: string
}
```

#### chunk - Streaming Content

```typescript
{
  type: "chunk",
  turnId: string,
  seq: number,       // Sequence number (0, 1, 2, ...)
  chunk: ChunkData   // See chunk types below
}

interface ChunkData {
  type: "content" | "thinking" | "thinking_xml" | "tool_call" | "error" | "status" | "task_completed";
  content?: string;
  data?: any;
}
```

#### turn_finished - Turn Completed

```typescript
{
  type: "turn_finished",
  turnId: string,
  ok: boolean,
  error?: string,
  summary?: string  // Optional session summary
}
```

## Chunk Type Details

### content - Response Text

```typescript
{
  type: "chunk",
  turnId: "abc-123",
  seq: 0,
  chunk: {
    type: "content",
    content: "Here's the analysis you requested..."
  }
}
```

### thinking - Reasoning Process

```typescript
{
  type: "chunk",
  turnId: "abc-123",
  seq: 1,
  chunk: {
    type: "thinking",
    content: "Let me analyze the requirements first..."
  }
}
```

### thinking_xml - Structured Thinking

```typescript
{
  type: "chunk",
  turnId: "abc-123",
  seq: 2,
  chunk: {
    type: "thinking_xml",
    content: "<thinking>\n  <step>1. Parse request</step>\n  <step>2. Identify tools</step>\n</thinking>"
  }
}
```

### tool_call - Tool Execution Request

```typescript
{
  type: "chunk",
  turnId: "abc-123",
  seq: 3,
  chunk: {
    type: "tool_call",
    data: {
      name: "readFile",
      parameters: {
        path: "/path/to/file.txt"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

### error - Error Message

```typescript
{
  type: "chunk",
  turnId: "abc-123",
  seq: 4,
  chunk: {
    type: "error",
    content: "File not found: /path/to/file.txt"
  }
}
```

### status - Status Update

```typescript
{
  type: "chunk",
  turnId: "abc-123",
  seq: 5,
  chunk: {
    type: "status",
    content: "Reading file (1/3)..."
  }
}
```

### task_completed - Task Complete

```typescript
{
  type: "chunk",
  turnId: "abc-123",
  seq: 6,
  chunk: {
    type: "task_completed",
    data: {
      ok: true,
      summary: "Task completed successfully"
    }
  }
}
```

## Connection Lifecycle

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant U as UI (Ink/Web)
    participant D as Daemon
    
    U->>D: WebSocket Connection
    D->>U: open event
    
    U->>D: {"type": "hello", "client": "ink"}
    D->>U: {"type": "hello", "daemonVersion": "1.0.0"}
    
    U->>D: {"type": "start_turn", "input": "Hello"}
    D->>U: {"type": "turn_started", "sessionId": "sess-123", "turnId": "turn-1"}
    
    loop Streaming
        D->>U: {"type": "chunk", "chunk": {"type": "content", ...}}
        D->>U: {"type": "chunk", "chunk": {"type": "thinking", ...}}
    end
    
    D->>U: {"type": "turn_finished", "ok": true}
    
    Note over U,D: Repeat for subsequent turns
    
    U->>D: {"type": "cancel_turn", "turnId": "turn-5"}
    
    U->>D: close event
    D->>U: close event
```

## Auto-Reconnect Logic

```typescript
class WebSocketClient {
    private reconnectDelay = 750;
    private maxRetries = 10;
    
    connect() {
        this.ws = new WebSocket(`ws://localhost:${FF_TERMINAL_PORT}`);
        
        this.ws.onclose = () => {
            this.scheduleReconnect();
        };
        
        this.ws.onerror = (error) => {
            console.error('WebSocket error:', error);
        };
    }
    
    scheduleReconnect() {
        setTimeout(() => {
            this.connect();
        }, this.reconnectDelay);
    }
}
```

## Port Configuration

| Component | Default Port | Variable |
|-----------|-------------|----------|
| Daemon | 28888 | `FF_TERMINAL_PORT` |
| Web Client | 8787 | `FF_WEB_PORT` |
| FieldView | 8788 | `FF_FIELDVIEW_PORT` |

## Error Handling

| Error Code | Description | Action |
|------------|-------------|--------|
| `ECONNREFUSED` | Daemon not running | Auto-reconnect |
| `ETIMEDOUT` | Request timeout | Retry or show error |
| `EINVALID` | Invalid message format | Log error, ignore |
| `EUNAUTHORIZED` | Missing auth | Show auth prompt |

